{You would have opened 1\D but after North opens 1NT you must pass.

Partner bids 2\H in the balancing seat.  

The 2\H bid shows \Hs and \Ss.

You have absolutely no preference between the two suits. But you do have a preference as to where the opening lead will be coming from - you'd like South to have to lead through North's strength. Besides you feel like playing the last hand so you say 2\S and everybody passes.}

